'''Evram Lajaie''' was a [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Commander/Legends|commander]] of the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]]. In [[0 BBY/Legends|0 BBY]], he was at the [[Great Temple/Legends|Alliance's base]] on [[Yavin 4/Legends|Yavin 4]]. When [[General/Legends|General]] [[Jan Dodonna/Legends|Jan Dodonna]], the base's commander, received the [[Death Star plans/Legends|secret plans]] for the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire's]] [[DS-1 Orbital Battle Station/Legends|Death Star]] [[Superweapon/Legends|superweapon]], Lajaie's expertise in both [[Realspace/Legends|space]] defense and [[Orbit/Legends|orbital]] [[Battle station/Legends|battle stations]] enabled him to quickly uncover a fatal flaw in the design of the [[Death Star/Legends|Death Star]]. Lajaie then attended a meeting where Dodonna discussed those findings with the base's [[Starfighter/Legends|starfighter]] [[Squadron/Legends|squadrons]], and the General organized an [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|attack]] on the Imperial superweapon. During the subsequent [[Space warfare/Legends|space battle]], [[Rebel pilot/Legends|Rebel pilot]] [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] successfully destroyed the Death Star, and Lajaie was present in a ceremony honoring Skywalker and other [[Heroes of Yavin/Legends|heroes]] of the battle.

==Biography==
The [[Human/Legends|Human]]<ref name="anh" /> Evram Lajaie served as a [[Commander/Legends|commander]] in the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]].<ref name="CCG">{{CCG|set=A New Hope Limited|cardname=Commander Evram Lajaie}}</ref> In [[0 BBY/Legends|0 BBY]], he<ref name="CSWE" /> was present in the [[Great Temple/Legends|Great Temple]], the Alliance's base on the [[Moon/Legends|moon]] [[Yavin 4/Legends|Yavin 4]]. That [[Standard year/Legends|year]], the base's commander, [[General/Legends|General]] [[Jan Dodonna/Legends|Jan Dodonna]], received the [[Death Star plans/Legends|secret plans]] for the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire's]] [[Superweapon/Legends|superweapon]], the [[DS-1 Orbital Battle Station/Legends|first Death Star]] [[Battle station/Legends|battle station]].<ref name="anh" /> Dodonna, along with Lajaie and others, frantically searched for possibilities to destroy the [[Space station/Legends|station]],<ref name="FF">{{FactFile|67|MIL 5-8|Escape of the ''Millennium Falcon''}}</ref> and Lajaie's expertise in [[Realspace/Legends|space]] defense and [[Orbit/Legends|orbital]] battlestations enabled him to quickly analyze the [[Death Star/Legends|Death Star]] plans. After careful analysis, Lajaie discovered a fatal flaw in the Death Star's design<ref name="CSWE" />&mdash;a weakness in its [[Thermal exhaust port/Legends|thermal exhaust port]] vulnerable to [[Proton torpedo/Legends|proton torpedo]] assault.<ref name="anh" />

[[File:Rogues_Gallery.jpg|thumb|left|Lajaie was present at the ceremony of awarding the Medal of Bravery to the Heroes of Yavin.]]
Lajaie was present in a briefing where Dodonna both discussed the findings and arranged for the base's [[Starfighter/Legends|starfighter]] [[Squadron/Legends|squadrons]] to launch an [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|attack]] on the Death Star. During the battle that followed, Lajaie was present alongside Dodonna in the base's command center monitoring the [[Space warfare/Legends|space battle]]. Eventually, the battle was won when [[Rebel pilot/Legends|Rebel pilot]] [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] destroyed the Death Star by firing proton torpedoes into the thermal exhaust port, causing a chain reaction that destroyed the whole Death Star. Following the battle, Lajaie was present in a ceremony when the [[Medal of Bravery/Legends|Medal of Bravery]] was awarded to Skywalker, [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]], and [[Chewbacca/Legends|Chewbacca]].<ref name="anh" />

==Personality and traits==
Evram Lajaie was a popular Alliance leader.<ref name="CCG" /> Because of his<ref name="CSWE" /> special<ref name="BtM">''[[Star Wars: Behind the Magic]]''</ref> expertise of space defense and orbital battlestations, Lajaie quickly made the discovery that allowed Luke Skywalker to destroy the Death Star.<ref name="CSWE" /> Lajaie had [[Color/Legends|gray]] [[Hair/Legends|hair]] and fair skin.<ref name="anh" />

==Equipment==
Lajaie wore the same [[Alliance military uniform/Legends|uniform]] as the other officers present in the Great Temple.<ref name="anh" />

==Behind the scenes==
Evram Lajaie first appeared as an uncredited Rebel extra in the Yavin 4 scenes of the [[1977]] film [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'': Episode IV ''A New Hope'']], including the ending ceremony honoring the [[Heroes of Yavin/Legends|Heroes of Yavin]].<ref name="anh" /> In [[1993]], ''[[The Farlander Papers]]'', a booklet accompanying the [[Star Wars video games|video game]] [[Star Wars: X-Wing (video game)|''Star Wars: X-Wing'']] released simultaneously, included an [[in-universe]] edited image taken from the ''A New Hope'' film scenes of Dodonna's briefing prior to the Battle of Yavin. With Lajaie's extra being included in that image, the photo is a briefing on the [[MC80A Home One Type Heavy Star Cruiser/Legends|MC80 ''Home One'' type Star Cruiser]] [[Independence/Legends|''Independence'']] prior to an Alliance [[Battle in the Turkana system|mission]] to the [[Turkana system/Legends|Turkana system]]. However, it is not confirmed if Lajaie is the character in that edited photo in-universe.<ref name="TFP">{{StoryCite|story=The Farlander Papers|book=Star Wars: X-Wing (video game)}}</ref> The character was first identified by name, and given a brief back-story, in the [[1996]] ''[[A New Hope Limited]]'' expansion set of the [[Star Wars Customizable Card Game|''Star Wars'' Customizable Card Game]].<ref name="CCG" />

